  "prompt": "Can you see someone's status message if they block you on WhatsApp?",
  "response": "When someone blocks you on WhatsApp, it restricts various forms of interaction and visibility between you and that person. Specifically regarding **status messages**, here's what happens:\n\n1. **Inaccessibility of Status Updates**: \n   - **You cannot see their current or any past status updates**. WhatsApp statuses (often referred to as \"Story\" in other platforms) are visible to users who are not blocked. Once you're blocked, these updates become invisible to you.\n\n2. **Profile Information Hidden**:\n   - You also lose access to their **last seen**, **online status**, and any **profile picture updates**. Essentially, all personal updates and statuses they share are concealed from you.\n\n3. **Messaging Restrictions**:\n   - Any messages you try to send to a person who has blocked you will show a single gray checkmark (message sent) but not a double checkmark (message delivered). Likewise, you won't receive any messages or calls from them.\n\n4. **Group Chats**:\n   - If you're both part of the same WhatsApp group, you can still see each other's messages within that group. Blocking mainly affects direct one-on-one interactions.\n\n5. **Third-Party Workarounds**:\n   - Some users might suggest using alternate methods or third-party apps to bypass these restrictions. **It's important to note** that using such methods can violate WhatsApp's terms of service and potentially compromise your privacy and security.\n\n**In summary**, if someone has blocked you on WhatsApp, you will **not** be able to see their status messages or any other personal updates they share on the platform.",
